Thousands of USA supporters packed fan parks across the country on Thursday to cheer on the team during their last Group G clash against Germany

With Butler Field in Chicago full of people 15 minutes ahead of the big kick-off, the support Jurgen Klinsmann's side have received from home fans during this tournament shows just how big football is becoming Stateside.

Those packed inside will have been disappointed with the 1-0 defeat at the hands of Germany but will have been delighted to progress after Portugal's 2-1 win over Ghana wasn't enough to see Cristiano Ronaldo and co go through.

