And the 
fans are embracing the success. Over seven years on from when David 
Beckham's move to LA Galaxy heralded a new era - that didn't quite work 
out - for soccer in the world's third largest country by population, 
football, as it is increasingly being referred to, is finally capturing 
the imagination of the fans.

Even the absence of Landon Donovan - considered a national hero in soccer terms - has not dampened the enthusiasm.

